SIMPLE: marker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marker
<hw>Mark"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who or that which
marks.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One who keeps account of a
game played, as of billiards.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A counter used in
card playing and other games.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>The soldier who forms the pilot of a wheeling column, or marks the
direction of an alignment.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>An attachment to a
sewing machine for marking a line on the fabric by creasing
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Market</ent>⟦br⟧
